Bring water and salt to a boil in a 4-quart pot. Add Broccoflower(R) florets and cook for three minutes. Remove from heat, drain, and put in ice water to stop cooking. Drain well and place in serving dish. In a small saucepan saute onion and peppers in 1-tablespoon olive oil until onions are transparent. Add balsamic vinegar and tarragon. Bring to a boil and remove from heat. Whisk in remaining olive oil. Pour over Broccoflower(R), toss to combine and refrigerate.